Alternatively, the fastest way — run this in the **SQL Editor**:

```sql
ALTER TABLE companies DISABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE website_snapshots DISABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE website_changes DISABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
```

Run that and let me know!

The issue is that the tables were created without granting permissions to the API roles. Run this in the **SQL Editor**:

```sql
GRANT ALL ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO service_role;
GRANT ALL ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO anon;
GRANT ALL ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO authenticated;
```

